title: Victory with a Garland, Sala di Recezione, Palazzo Quirinale, Rome
provenance: Giovanni Piancastelli; Mr. and Mrs. Edward D. Brandegee
medium:
Pen and dark gray ink, brush and color washes over black chalk ruled lines on beige wove paper
Support: beige wove paper
description: Fame raises garlands in both hands. On her left, putto with cornucopia; on her right, putto with garland. On ground at left, garland and trumpet; at right, garland and thyrsus. Ruled lines in black chalk suggest rectangular moldings.
name: Drawing
